Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Trim the @aubergine{1} then
halve lengthways. Chop each half into four long strips, then chop widthways into
roughly 2cm pieces. Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}. Trim the @pak choi{1} then
separate the leaves. Slice each leaf lengthways into halves.

Pop the aubergine onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and the @honey{1%tsp},
then sprinkle over the @Indonesian style spice mix{1}. Season with @salt{} and
@black pepper{} and toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven
is hot, roast on the top shelf until the aubergine is soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #medium saucepan{} on medium-high heat.
When hot, add the @yellow Thai style paste{2} and stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.
Add the @coconut milk{200%ml}, @water{450%ml} for the sauce, @vegetable stock paste{10%g}
and @peanut butter{1%tbsp}. Bring to a boil, then lower the heat and simmer for
~{10%minutes}.

While the soup simmers, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Once it has simmered for
~{10%minutes}, add the @egg noodle nest{2} and the pak choi. Cook until tender,
~{4%minutes}.

> TIP: Add more water if the noodles soak up the liquid too much.

Taste the noodle soup and season with @salt{}, @black pepper{} and the juice and
zest of half the lime.

Share the noodle soup between your #bowls{}. Top with the roasted aubergine.
Sprinkle over the chopped peanuts and serve with any remaining lime chopped
into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!